On Fri, 14 Mar 2008, Steve Maziarz wrote:

> I'm getting ready to install new seat covers that I just received from
> Sewfine.
> Should I replace the draw string with stainless steel wire?
> Where can I purchase stainless steel wire and what type should I get - solid
> or stranded?  What gauge?

Here you go!

http://www.aircraftspruce.com/catalog/appages/safetywire.php

You can find the good stuff at aircraft supply places if you come up empty
at the local hardware store.

> I do not have the original rods that were used in the old upholstery. Any
> reason I can't use
> metal coat hangers or welding rods.

The wires have to be pretty stiff, so coat hangers are out.  1/8 steel gas
welding rods might be just the ticket.

